Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Drain the @mozzarella{1} and tear into small chunks. Arrange your @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} (2 per person) on #baking trays{} and cover with the @tomato puree{60} leaving a 1cm border round the edge. Share the @chorizo{60}(diced) and mozzarella between the tortillas.

Bake the tortizzas in the oven until golden and the cheese is bubbly ~{7-8%mins}.

Meanwhile drain and rinse the @black beans{1/2}. Zest, then halve the @lime{1}. Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}. Thinly slice the @green chilli{1/2}. 

> TIP: Halve lengthways and remove the seeds first if you don't like things too spicy!

Roughly chop the @coriander{1} (stalks and all).

Slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the insides onto your #chopping board{}. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Mix the black beans, avocado, lime zest and half the spring onion together in a #large bowl{}. Add in juice of your lime(s) and the @olive oil{1}. Mix well and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep to one side.

When the tortizzas are ready, pop them onto your plates. Serve the salsa on top and finish with a sprinkle of coriander, remaining spring onion and as much chilli as you like! Enjoy!